    <title>Special Limit Laws (LT7)</title>
    <objectives>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <xi:include href="outcomes/07.ptx" />
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives>
    <subsection>
        <title>Special Limit Laws</title>
        <p>Recall the Squeeze Theorem <xref ref="squeeze-thm" />.</p>


        <activity>
            <introduction>
                <p>The area of a circular sector is given by <m>\frac{r^2 \theta}{2}</m>, where <m>r</m>
                    is the radius of the circle and <m>\theta</m> is the angle of the sector. In
                    this activity we will use the geometry of this Figure and <xref
                        ref="squeeze-thm" /> to obtain the important limits <md>
                        <mrow>\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin(x)}{x} \amp = 1</mrow>
                        <mrow>\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\cos(x) - 1}{x} \amp = 0 </mrow>
                    </md>
                    .</p>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <figure>
                        <caption>Testing</caption>
                        <interactive xml:id="interactive-jsx-squeeze" source="squeeze.js"
                            platform="jsxgraph">
                            <slate xml:id="jsx-squeeze" surface="jsxboard" />
                        </interactive>
                    </figure>
                    <p>
                        Find a chain of inequalities relating the areas of sector ADE, triangle ADC,
                        and
                        sector ABC in Figure.
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>Divide your inequalities by an appropriate positive number so that the middle
                        term is of the form <m>\sin(x)/x</m>.</p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task xml:id="task-sinx-x">
                <statement>
                    <p>Use the squeeze theorem to conclude that <m>\lim_{x\to 0} \sin(x)/x = 1</m>.</p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>Multiply the expression <me>
                            \frac{\cos(x) - 1}{x}
                        </me> on top and
                        bottom so that the top becomes an expression involving <m>\sin(x)</m>.</p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>Use limit laws and the result of <xref ref="task-sinx-x" /> to deduce that <m>\lim_{x\to
                        0} \frac{\cos(x) - 1}{x} = 0</m>.</p>
                </statement>
            </task>
        </activity>
    </subsection>
</section>
